Here is the Native Memory Core implementation.

This module is not just a simulation; it performs actual heap allocation to reserve the context window. It uses a Ring Buffer (Circular Buffer) architecture, which is the standard for managing sliding context windows in LLM inference engines (FIFO - First In, First Out).

1. The Architecture
The memory module operates on a "Hot-Swap" basis. When you switch from 32k to 128k, the engine performs a secure memory dump of the current context, reallocates the heap, and attempts to re-inject the previous conversation history into the new window.

